You’re getting this error because `MKPlacemark` apparently expects you to supply a `CLLocationCoordinate2D` to one of the `init` methods that have `coordinate` parameter. E.g.:

    let coordinate = CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: ..., longitude: ...)
    let placemark = MKPlacemark(coordinate: coordinate)

One can imagine that the author of the `MKPlacemark` never contemplated someone creating a placemark that doesn’t actually represent some coordinate. Clearly, it would be nice if `MKPlacemark` handled this error more gracefully, but, alas, it doesn’t. You should feel free to [report feedback to Apple][1] on this behavior, if you want.


  [1]: https://feedbackassistant.apple.com

